\f0\fs30 I had never really touched another person before the re-enactments. Touching my mother was different- that was a part of my being because I had to do for her in every way. She lost mobility to help herself when I was about 10, and being a beanpole of a child helped- I could reach all the way across the country of her flesh to clean her.
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs30  
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs30  In many ways I was an adult before I was a child, in that same way you see children who dance on television. Their responses, while rehearsed carefully over and over seem as though they are awkwardly stuck on, a skin suit that doesn\'92t quite fit and somehow makes the fine movements of children grosser and less able.
\f1\fs24 \

